		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Glory of Heracles IV - SNES Translation fix?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How big is the ROM file in bytes? Is it an even multiple of 524288 bytes (4 Mbit), or is it a multiple of 524288 bytes plus 512 bytes? Newer emulators don't need 512-byte headers that were added by obsolete floppy disk-based copiers. If it has the copier header, chop off the first 512 bytes in a hex editor and rename the file to end in <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.sfc</tt> (headerless Super Famicom ROM image), as opposed to a copier-specific extension such as <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.smc</tt>, <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.swc</tt>, or <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.fig</tt>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


